How should undo redo of float input or any other text input be handled be handled
ideas
When a modification is found (compare state before gui and after gui) save the state. When the modification is finished then create an action.
One issue is what does when modification is finished mean.
If you just assume when the input is deactiated then things like this break.
Click the input
Start writing
press ctrl+z
No action will be saved, so it will revert the action done before clicking the input.
To handle this case I guess you could process the ctrl+z some way so it create an action and the the actual ctrl+z would undo it.

Could do something with combining actions if there are 2 consecutive actions that modify the same field.

Google search forgets the redo undo after you unfocus.

