Serialization versioning.
Could put the number version on the whole file. Don't really see an advantage of putting in on smaller parts of the file as it is impossible to have parts of a file saved with different version numbers.
Because json is used adding a new field (with a default value) doesn't break backwards and forwards compatibility.
Removing a field would break backwards compatiblity (old versions can't load the new file), but doesn't break forwards compatiblity.
If there is some change that can't be handled this easily then make 2 versions of the struct with the breaking change and load based on version.

